  <description value="Quantitified type representing  scientific  quantities, i.e. quantities expressed as a magnitude and units. Units are expressed in the UCUM syntax (http://unitsofmeasure.org/ucum.html[Unified Code for Units of Measure (UCUM)], by Gunther Schadow and Clement J. McDonald of The Regenstrief Institute)  (case-sensitive form) by default, or another system if `_units_system_` is set. &#xA;&#xA;Can also be used for time durations, where it is more convenient to treat these as simply a number of seconds rather than days, months, years (in the latter case, `DV_DURATION` may be used)."/>
  <jurisdiction>
    <coding>
      <system value="http://unstats.un.org/unsd/methods/m49/m49.htm"/>
      <code value="001"/>
    </coding>
  </jurisdiction>
